# Phase 5: Transport & Orchestration Plan

Refining the system to support remote agents and orchestrate workflows via N8N.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Transport Mode**: I will modify [src/index.ts](file:///home/gonya/antigravity-mcp-server/src/index.ts) to support running in either `stdio` (default) or `http` (SSE) mode based on a command-line argument (e.g., `--transport=sse`). This allows simultaneous use by local clients (VS Code) and remote agents (via Ngrok).

## Proposed Changes

### [src/index.ts](file:///home/gonya/antigravity-mcp-server/src/index.ts)
- Introduce argument parsing (e.g., `process.argv`).
- If `--transport=sse` (or `http`) is passed:
    - Start Express server.
    - Setup `SSEServerTransport`.
- Else (default):
    - Start `StdioServerTransport`.

### N8N Configuration
- Inspect running N8N instance (processes, config files).
- Verify Docker permission for the user running N8N.

## Verification Plan

### Automated
- Run `node dist/index.js --transport=sse` and check if port 3000 opens.
- Run `node dist/index.js` (std/defaults) and check if it waits for input.

### Manual
- User to test accessing the SSE endpoint.
